</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="2D8B2A11063F2E73FC4EFCF5FBFE24BE" box="[961,1044,474,500]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[332,1255,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@22.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Cryptodromia tuberculata Stimpson, 1858, male with sponge cap, 14.3 × 12.9 mm (WAM C 11733): A, dorsal view; B, frontal view, with sponge cap; C, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501051/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65063F2E73FBAAFCF5FB2D24BE" author="Alcock, A." box="[1061,1223,474,500]" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" pagination="123 - 169" refId="ref24584" refString="Alcock, A. (1900) Materials for a carcinological Fauna of India. No. 5. Brachyura Primigenia or Dromiacea. Journal of the Asiatic Society Bengal, 1899, 68 (2), 123 - 169. [1900]" type="journal article" year="1900">Alcock (1900)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17063F2E73FAB5FCF4FF562752" authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1901" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pileifera">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FAB5FCF4FF562752" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">C. pileifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a sub-species of 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17063F2E73FEF3FCD0FDF62752" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[380,540,510,537]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FEF3FCD0FDF62752" box="[380,540,510,537]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">C. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in 1901 treated as a separate species. Comparison shows that in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17063F2E73FA92FCD0FA762752" authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1901" box="[1309,1436,510,537]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pileifera">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FA92FCD0FA762752" box="[1309,1436,510,537]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">C. pileifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there are four evenly spaced anterolateral carapace teeth, with the last pair weaker (three teeth second and third separated by an edentate convex margin in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17063F2E73FDFAFF68FCFF272A" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[629,789,582,609]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FDFAFF68FCFF272A" box="[629,789,582,609]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">C. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the supraorbital margin is concave and weakly eave-like (supraorbital margin concave strongly eave-like), and the cheliped fingers are narrow, curved, gape slot-like (fingers stout, straighter, gape triangular). Both of these species have comparatively large eggs and 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17063F2E73FB2FFFA0FACB27E2" authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1901" box="[1184,1313,654,681]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pileifera">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FB2FFFA0FACB27E2" box="[1184,1313,654,681]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">C. pileifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only has a single larval stage (Tan 
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FE12FF9CFE272786" box="[413,461,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">et al</emphasis>
. 1986). 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17063F2E73FDA8FF9DFCA12786" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[551,843,690,716]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FDA8FF9DFCA12786" box="[551,843,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Cryptodromia tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has even larger eggs (&gt; 
<quantity id="72489B71063F2E73FBDBFF9DFB432787" box="[1108,1193,690,717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
diameter) and so may well have an even shorter larval phase. Clutch size is correspondingly smaller, often with fewer than 
<specimenCount id="A3B6FD1D063F2E73FA8DFFF9FAB627BB" box="[1282,1372,726,753]" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" type="egg">10 eggs</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FDAA651F063F2E73FF48FFD5FB2E2672" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B50F3694063F2E73FF48FFD5FB2E2672" blockId="21.[151,1437,150,824]" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FF48FFD5FE8B265E" bold="true" box="[199,353,762,788]" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="CDA77604063F2E73FEE7FFD5FE4E265E" box="[360,420,762,788]" name="India" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="CDA77604063F2E73FE3FFFD5FDCE265E" box="[432,548,762,788]" name="Singapore" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, Southeast Asia, and 
<collectingCountry id="CDA77604063F2E73FC9CFFD5FC7F265E" box="[787,917,762,788]" name="Philippines" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Philippines</collectingCountry>
. The present material is a new record for 
<collectingCountry id="CDA77604063F2E73FAE9FFD5FF3E2672" name="Australia" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Australia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17063F2E73FF50FE31FE082672" authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1901" box="[223,482,798,824]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pileifera">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86063F2E73FF50FE31FE082672" box="[223,482,798,824]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Cryptodromia pileifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected intertidally and from shallow sub-tidal depths.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
